  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for the full spectrum of Human Resource functions which includes recruitment, payroll, administration, compensation and benefits, and any other HR related matters.</li><li>Handle end to end recruitment process which includes but not limited to job posting, resume screening, arrange interview and conduct interview with shortlisted candidates, extend offer and prepare LOA.</li><li>Handle internal and clients’ monthly payroll processing, CPF submission, AIS and IR21 submission and preparation of IR8A form, NSmen make-up claims, Government Paid Leave claim submission, etc.</li><li>Respond to queries on client's payroll related matters.</li><li>Process the employee life cycle which includes new staff onboarding, probation, confirmation, promotion/transfer process, exit interview and ensure any letter in regards to the employees are prepared in a timely manner.</li><li>Maintain and update employee information in HRIS (Info-Tech, Talenox).</li><li>Any other ad hoc duties as assigned by superior.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must possess minimum Diploma/Degree in Human Resource Management or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum 2 years' hands-on experience in the of recruitment and payroll function.</li><li>Proficient with Microsoft Office Applications.</li><li>Strong verbal & written communication and able to interact with people at all levels.</li><li>Meticulous and good working attitude.</li><li>Able to work independently or with minimal supervision.</li><li>Must have a good knowledge of labour legislation in Singapore.</li><li>Have regional knowledge of labour laws outside of Singapore is a plus.</li><li>Mandarin proficiency is is vital to liaise with Mandarin-speaking clients.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
